abstract: How Sanders can win, calls for Bolton to testify, Warren’s new line: This is your morning tip sheet.
snippet: How Sanders can win, calls for Bolton to testify, Warren’s new line: This is your morning tip sheet.
lead_paragraph: Chasten Buttigieg stood on a chair to snap a shot of his husband, Pete, amid a gaggle of reporters after a town hall event in Boone, Iowa, on Monday.

abstract: The U.S. State Department removed a National Public Radio reporter from the press pool for Secretary of State Mike Pompeo's upcoming foreign trip, a press association and NPR said on Monday, days after Pompeo angrily responded to another NPR journalist's interview with him.
snippet: The U.S. State Department removed a National Public Radio reporter from the press pool for Secretary of State Mike Pompeo's upcoming foreign trip, a press association and NPR said on Monday, days after Pompeo angrily responded to another NPR journ...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The U.S. State Department removed a National Public Radio reporter from the press pool for Secretary of State Mike Pompeo's upcoming foreign trip, a press association and NPR said on Monday, days after Pompeo angrily responded to another NPR journalist's interview with him.
headline_main: U.S. State Department Bars NPR Reporter From Pompeo Trip After Testy Interview
headline_print_headline: U.S. State Department Bars NPR Reporter From Pompeo Trip After Testy Interview

lead_paragraph: Gail Collins: Bret, there are only two subjects in our current political world: impeachment and the Democratic presidential race. Both are certainly … exciting.

abstract: With or without witnesses, Trump’s trial shows that the antifederalists were right to question the Senate’s purpose.
snippet: With or without witnesses, Trump’s trial shows that the antifederalists were right to question the Senate’s purpose.
lead_paragraph: Last week, after Senate Republicans voted unanimously to approve their leader Mitch McConnell’s rules for President Trump’s impeachment trial — fast-tracking the process and putting up barriers to the production of evidence and witnesses, Representative Jerry Nadler of New York, one of seven impeachment managers, despaired over the strong chance that voters would not get a fair, comprehensive hearing of the case against the president.

abstract: He doesn’t want a revolution. He doesn’t have a movement. He could still win this thing.
snippet: He doesn’t want a revolution. He doesn’t have a movement. He could still win this thing.
lead_paragraph: Joe Biden has no trouble lingering in place, wherever he is, especially if there’s a point he wants to finish — or start. Generally it does not matter how many people are prodding him along or waiting out in the cold. And it seemed important to Biden that I hear what he was talking about right now before we finished.

headline_main: The Method in John Bolton’s Madness

abstract: James Corden said Bolton, the former national security adviser, proves that Republicans can go against their party “as long as it’s perfectly timed with the release of a book.”

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Republicans lack the votes to block witnesses at President Donald Trump's impeachment trial, Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell conceded late Tuesday, a potentially major hurdle for Trump's hopes to end the trial with a quick acquittal. Earlier, Trump's lawyers concluded his defense with a plea to move on.
